text: This is my "go to" place for liquor purchase. The attendant is very sweet and knowledgeable. I bypass other places just to go to her.

name: Jess
text: Super overpriced! I earn good money. And I am not the kind of person who saves or coupons, however I lived in Atlanta for 3 years. You need money to live comfortably there. Yet vodka (Smirnoff) $9.99-12.99 tops for the large bottle. Hereits 19.99 or think a little more. That's ridiculous. It's just Smirnoff. Only reason I'm writing this review is bc there are only like 3 package stores in west mobile. And they are all overpriced. Miss Atlanta!

name: Brent John
text: Royal package store is one of the BEST in town. There is a great selection of beer and wine as well as liquor. The  liquor prices are a bit high but the service was friendly and outstanding!! It’s very convenient! Local guide!

name: Celia Williams
text: Huge selection, nice staff,  no stigma. I work at a stressful place and with this pandemic,  the last thing I need is to feel uncomfortable or degraded just for a bottle of wine. I'm a shy and easy going person who only gets things in person that I can't order from my phone. The staff were so warm and comforting. 10 stars. An extra few bucks is worth it to shop with a smile.
